Kind of document: Small web format?(SWF) or Adobe Flash document

MIME Type: application/xml?is recommended as of?RFC 7303?(section 4.1), but?text/xml?is still seen sometimes. A file with the extension?.xml?can often be given a more specific MIME type depending on how its contents are meant to be interpreted (for instance, an Atom feed is?application/atom+xml), but?application/xml?serves as a valid default.
